          <td bgcolor="" valign="top" width="1"><img src="/lotr/gfx/trans_header1.gif" width="0" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Galactic Quest / Buford, Ga 1/05/01<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.87)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=222'>Mike "Kessling" Kessling</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=222&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 6, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> The tournament started at 4 pm and was 5 games long. Adam Beauchamp, Trevor Bradley, Wesley Addison, and Chip Nicholson all came up from Griffin and picked me up from my house to go to the tournament. I was unsure on what Fellowship I wanted to play going into this tournament and I switched from &quot;Fighting Frodo&quot; to Gandalf to a deck that started Boromir and Merry (both rare)which Adam had built. <br>
The deck looked something like this:<br>
Start:<br>
Frodo, Son of Drogo<br>
The One Ring, Isildurs Bane<br>
Boromir - Rare<br>
Merry - Rare<br>
<br>
Companions:<br>
Aragorn - Rare x2<br>
<br>
Posessions:<br>
Rangers Sword x2<br>
Blade of Gondor x2<br>
Hobbit Sword x2<br>
Armor<br>
<br>
Conditions:<br>
A Talent for not being seen x2<br>
No Stranger to the Shadows x2<br>
<br>
Allies:<br>
Thrarin<br>
<br>
Events:<br>
Power According to His Stature x3<br>
Dagger Strike x4<br>
Hobbit Stealth x3<br>
Swordsman of the Northern Kingdom x4<br>
<br>
I realized that with this Fellowship I should play a Shadow deck that is geared towards killing companions for a victory, because my Fellowship is just meant to live, not win =p. So I decided upon an Uruk-Hai deck that utilized Sarmuans Snows because I don&#39;t own any Savagery to Match Their Numbers and Bred for Battle is such a balls card.<br>
<br>
The deck looked something like this:<br>
Minions - 21<br>
Lurtz x3<br>
Troop of Uruk-Hai x4<br>
Orthanc Assasin x4<br>
Uruk Shaman x3<br>
Uruk Warrior x4<br>
Uruk Lieutenant x3<br>
<br>
Conditions - 9:<br>
Sarumans Ambition x3<br>
Sarumans Snows x4<br>
Spies of Saruman x2<br>
<br>
Game One : Richard Hammond playing Nazgul/Sauron/Arwen and Legolas.<br>
<br>
I bid zero (I bid zero in every game today), I think he bid one. He chose for me to go first because his sites 2 and 3 are important for him. I ran to site two after pulling Aragorn, and I was met with a nazgul who dealt me minor damage and I stopped at site two, not wanting to face the Ford with one nazgul already out. He pulls Argorn and runs all the way to site three with me doing minimal damage to his Fellowship. We continue doing little damage to each other, but I am assembling a huge shadow hand. At site 8 I play enough Uruks to kill Aragorn, Legolas, and Arwen. When he runs to site 9 he plays Sam and Haldir, but I have enough minions to kill both of them and Frodo who was overwhelmed. Fw +3<br>
<br>
Body Count: 5 not counting Frodo<br>
<br>
Game 2 Me VS Trevor Bradley playing Gandalf and Uruk-Hai<br>
<br>
Basically the same fellowship moves for me this game. I manage to kill off something like 3 companions this game, not sure which ones. Basically it came down to at site 9 I regrouped when he ran and drew 6 fellowship, leaving me with only 2 or 3 minions on the table. Thrarin came up during the maneuver phase and OVERWHELMED a Troop of Uruk-Hai due to Servant of the Secret Fire x3 =p. It was a fun game atleast. FL +1<br>
<br>
Body Count: 8<br>
<br>
Game 3: Me VS Phillip Gladney&#39;s Random Fellowship and Uruk-Hai<br>
<br>
His Uruk-Hai do minimal damage to me all game as I avoid fights or just take wounds on Aragorn and Boromir. Going into site 9 he had Gandalf, Legolas, Arwen, Frodo, Sam, and I think Merry, most of which were exhausted. I killed one of them with archery damage, and all but Gandalf and Frodo with the first round of fights. Gandalf had killed off my Uruk-Warrior so I only had Lurtz fierce, and Lurtz killed Gandalf, leaving him only Frodo, Sting, and the Ring...but he still gets the win. Snows helped me a lot this game because at site 9 he couldn&#39;t have played anything or used bounder if he needed to. FL +1<br>
<br>
Body Count: 13<br>
<br>
Game 4: Me VS Scotty (don&#39;t know last name) playing a fellowship very similar to mine and Moria and Sauron orcs.<br>
<br>
Basically the same thing as last game, me killing all his companions at site 9 (3) and snows stops him from using Bounder at site 9 so Frodo is overwhelemed. You gotta love snows. Fw +3<br>
<br>
Game 5: Me VS Adam Beauchamp playing Gandalf/Tech Moria<br>
<br>
Adam got a hand full of Shadow and I got a hand full of my best cards. I should be extremely disadvantaged against Gandalf, and swarm is my hardest matchup, but sometimes luck has a big factor. He got out Aragorn and Legolas on the first turn and by site 4 both of them were dead. I killed Gandalf at site 5. He played Arwen and walked to site 6 or 7 and I killed both Arwen and Frodo. My Hobbit Stealth and Aragorn being Defender +1 really helped against the swarm due to his poor draw. FW + 3<br>
<br>
So I finish at +11. Trevor Bradley went undefeated, Phillip Gladney lost once, and Adam Beauchamp, Stephen Michael, someone else, and myself all lost 2 games. Wesley lost 2 games but had a timed win to put him at 10 victory points. Richard Hammond did the totals of who we played against, giving Adam Beauchamp 3rd place and me 4th place. I got two packs for my effort and busted a PATHS which I was pleased with.<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
Adam Drake - Becuase he is the man and he lent me the spies of saruman I neeeded<br>
Adam Beauchamp - Just for being BACON<br>
Wesley Addison - For being BACON<br>
Trevor Bradley - For Being the whole gosh darnit pig =p<br>
Chip - For being the Machine.<br>
Stephen Michael - for getting to good prize support to be given away (read: foil Witch King)<br>
<br>
Mike Kessling <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3236&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
